<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 8:08PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Alamance
and southwestern Orange Counties through 845 PM EDT...
At 808 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Graham, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Burlington, Graham, Mebane, Haw River, Swepsonville, Alamance, Lake
Mackintosh Marina, Sutphin, Cane Creek Reservoir and Saxapahaw.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
